#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:2
msgid "Software vulnerabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:4
msgid ""
"Security issues with software installed on machines are monitored using a"
" platform-specific process. Our processes (and specifically timelines) to"
" mitigate vulnerabilities depend on the support status of the respective "
"platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:7
msgid ""
"When mitigating a vulnerability we may choose different strategies "
"depending on the situation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:10
msgid ""
"Ideally we will update the package to an unaffected version that stays "
"API compatible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:13
msgid ""
"We may update to a package with API incompatibility but will help our "
"customers to fix breakage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:16
msgid ""
"We may stay on the existing version and include a patch provided by the "
"vendor, security researchers, other distributions or other sources we "
"deem trustworthy after a review."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:20
msgid ""
"We may contain the effect of the vulnerability by disabling features, "
"adjusting configuration, firewalling or other measures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:23
msgid ""
"We may choose to ignore the security vulnerability if the impact or "
"attack vectors are not relevant on our platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:26
msgid "We might take other actions not listed here, depending on the situation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:30
msgid "NixOS 19.03"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:32
msgid ""
"We actively monitor our code base and the packages that are actually "
"installed on customer systems (excluding user environments) for matches "
"against public vulnerability databases (i.e. NIST CVE)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:36
msgid ""
"We perform a scan for new vulnerabilities once a week and create work "
"tickets with different priorities based on multiple criteria of the "
"vulnerability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:39
msgid ""
"As we included some packages from the upstream NixOS unstable branch we "
"regularly keep this branch updated and thus include security fixed "
"provided by the NixOS community in a timely manner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:45
msgid "NixOS 15.09 (outdated)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:47
msgid ""
"No security updates are provided. Customers in need of guaranteed "
"security updates are advised to update to NixOS 19.03."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:51
msgid "Gentoo (outdated)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.rst:53
msgid ""
"We provide selective security updates by reviewing the published list of "
"Gentoo Linux Security Advisories (GLSA) every 2 months and selecting "
"critical security updates where necessary."
msgstr ""

